CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 24, 1951, pg. 18 reads: "Next Stop Farrell - Westinghouse High School's crack cage squad is shown eyeing the basket prior to their cage tilt with Sharpsville at Pitt Stadium Wednesday night. By winning, 69-45, the Bulldogs gained the right to meet Farrell for the Western Class A title next week.  From left to right the players are: Bill Peatross, Tom DeStefano, Ed Fleming, Maurice Stokes, John Miller, Bob McMasters and Larry Prunty. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Westinghouse High School basketball players, posed from left: Bill Peatross, Tom DeStefano, Ed Fleming, Maurice Stokes, John Miller, Bob McMasters, and Larry Prunty
